message: I'm a big fan of http://www.millenniumrestaurant.com/ Its kinda fancy, but I'm a huge carnivore and I still loved the place a ton.

I'm a native of NYC's Lower East Side and East Village.  I had lots of awesome Vegetarian and Vegan options available to me.  What is the best here in San Francisco?  I really need too find a good Veggie restaurant.

I'm a vegetarian and I love the following all-veggie restaurants: they are all actually within a two block radius in the Valencia corridor - Herbivore (very eclectic - the seitan shawarma is good), Dosa (any dosa), Udipi (South Indian), Gracias Madre (get the sampler plate) & Chaya (Japanese - get the noodle bowls)
Oh and go to Pappa Lotte on 24th & Valencia - get the super veggie burrito :-)

Here's a list of vegetarian-friendly (some serve meat too) restaurants in the City, broken down by type of restaurant. And you can add to it if you fork and send a pull request https://github.com/mojombo/sf-vegetarian-restaurants
I'm a big fan of Ananda Fuara - http://www.yelp.com/biz/ananda-fuara-san-francisco
Go to Gracias Madre in the mission. You'll love it.
I like The Plant organic cafe. They have a couple of locations in the City.
Millennium and Greens get this omnivore's vote. I really, really don't like Gracias Madre. They try to force too many dishes, and it just doesn't work.
as someone who only eats meat and judges everyone who is vegetarian, I would eat here without a bribe. http://www.enjoyveggie.com/
